1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,480
A few days ago, I shared a simple background remover tool on Reddit.

2
00:00:04,480 --> 00:00:08,000
While many liked the simplicity, one user, Adventurous,

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:13,760
date 9971, pointed out something crucial. In the real world, especially for e-commerce

4
00:00:13,760 --> 00:00:18,400
sellers and photographers, it's not just about the AI model, it's about the workflow.

5
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:23,520
They mentioned that using tools like GIMP with PYAutoGUI was a nightmare.

6
00:00:23,520 --> 00:00:27,360
So, I decided to fix the pain points they mentioned.

7
00:00:27,440 --> 00:00:33,040
Today, I am updating the BG underscore remover with a focus on professional utility.

8
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:36,799
First, the tool now mirrors your entire folder structure.

9
00:00:36,799 --> 00:00:41,599
If you drop a folder with 10 subdirectories, the output will look exactly the same,

10
00:00:41,599 --> 00:00:45,360
preserving your organization. Second, I've ensured that original

11
00:00:45,360 --> 00:00:49,680
file names are kept intact to avoid confusion in product management.

12
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:55,200
Third, I added a Review Needed feature. If the AI is unsure about a cutout,

13
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:59,200
it automatically moves that file to a separate folder for manual inspection,

14
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:01,279
saving you from hunting through hundreds of images.

15
00:01:01,840 --> 00:01:06,239
Finally, as a developer who loves data, I've integrated a local log that tracks

16
00:01:06,239 --> 00:01:12,000
processing time and hardware performance. This helps you see if switching to a dedicated GPU

17
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:14,720
actually makes a difference for your specific batch.

18
00:01:14,720 --> 00:01:18,000
The updated source code is available on my GitHub.

19
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:23,680
If you find this workflow improvement helpful, please consider leaving a star on the repository.

20
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:27,440
Your conscientious support is what keeps this project evolving.


